HEADWORD: Hipparion
<hw>Hip*pa"ri*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ a pony, dim. of <?/ a horse.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An
extinct genus of Tertiary mammals allied to the horse, but three-toed,
having on each foot a small lateral hoof on each side of the main
central one. It is believed to be one of the ancestral genera of the
Horse family.</def></p>

